<font color="#FF0000">INRE TO COOK</font><br>
<tt>Mon Jun 30 15:11:30 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
You know, Cook, I was sitting in a bar the other night, and this young kid comes up to me and asks me if I served in Vietnam.  I said yes, I did, and he puts his arms around me and gives me a hug and says, &quot;you helped saved my life.&quot;  He bought me a drink and said he was in Desert Storm, and thanks to Vietnam veterans, his tour was made easier.  I think I understand why he felt that way, now.  When Desert Storm was happening, I couldn't keep my TV off of CNN.  Why?  I don't know.  I had very mixed feelings about it, about the attention those veterans recieved and the parades and all.  But now, in retrospect (especially after what that guy told me the other night), I think I finally understand it all.  We did the right thing, 30 years ago, and I'm proud of my service, too.  But you said it all, Cook.<br>

